# V5.2.6 Walkthrough: Advanced Grid Popout & Ref# Syncing

I have implemented the advanced window detachment system and dynamic account renaming for RoboLedger V5.2.6.

## 🔗 Ref# & Pill Syncing
Renaming the account reference in the Action Bar now instantly propagates to the account switcher pills. This allows for rapid, unique identification of autodetected bank accounts.

```javascript
// Sync logic from app.js
window.handleRefUpdate = (newRef) => {
    const result = window.RoboLedger.Accounts.setRef(activeAcc.id, newRef.trim());
    if (result.success) {
      window.render(); // Pill refresh
      // ...
    }
}
```

## 🚀 Surgical Grid Popout
You can now detach the transaction grid into a standalone browser window.

### Key Features:
- **Blob URL Strategy**: No server-side files; the popout is generated dynamically via a Blob URL.
- **Bidirectional Sync**: Edits made in the popout window are sent back to the main window via `postMessage`, updating the Ledger Truth Vault in real-time.
- **Visual Parity**: The popout grid inherits the main app's CSS, including the **Rainbow Header** and color-coded amounts.
- **Pop-In Bridge**: A heartbeat monitor automatically restores the local grid if the popout window is closed or "Docked".

